  "prompt": "I just registered my first domain name, now what?",
  "response": "Congratulations on registering your first domain name! Here are some next steps:\n\n1. Choose a Web Hosting Provider\n- Compare hosting options (shared, VPS, dedicated)\n- Consider factors like price, reliability, and support\n- Popular hosts include Bluehost, HostGator, SiteGround\n\n2. Set Up DNS\n- Point your domain to your web hosting nameservers\n- This typically involves updating DNS settings at your domain registrar\n\n3. Decide on Website Platform\n- WordPress\n- Wix\n- Squarespace\n- Custom HTML/CSS\n- E-commerce platforms like Shopify\n\n4. Design Your Website\n- Create content\n- Choose a theme or design\n- Add pages (Home, About, Contact, etc.)\n\n5. Additional Recommended Steps\n- Set up professional email using your domain\n- Install SSL certificate for security\n- Configure Google Analytics\n- Set up basic SEO\n- Create social media accounts\n\n6. Optional but Helpful\n- Install security plugins\n- Regular backups\n- Performance optimization\n\n7. Launch and Promote\n- Test website functionality\n- Share on social media\n- Consider initial marketing strategies\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any of these steps?",
